!!! `<$waveform-editor>`

A canvas-based visual waveform editor for precisely selecting and editing audio regions. Typically used within a notation tiddler to refine the start/end times of an annotation.

---

!!!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Description |h
|`audio-source` |`""` |Tiddler title or URL of the audio file. Resolved via `resolveAudioSrc`. |
|`startTime` |`0` |Initial start time (seconds). |
|`endTime` |`0` |Initial end time (seconds). |
|`tiddler` |`""` |Tiddler to persist start/end times to (writes `start-seconds`, `end-seconds`, `start-timecode`, `end-timecode` fields). |
|`width` |`600` |Canvas width in CSS pixels. |
|`height` |`120` |Canvas height in CSS pixels. |
|`zoomPadding` |`10` |Seconds of padding around the region when zooming. |

---

!!!! Visual Features

* ''Waveform peaks'' rendered from decoded audio data
* ''Selected region'' highlighted with colored overlay and recolored peaks
* ''Draggable handles'' with triangular markers at top and bottom
* ''Play button'' centered in the region (when region is wide enough)
* ''Minimap'' below the main canvas showing the full track with viewport indicator
* ''Tooltip'' showing the time at the cursor position
* ''Listen mode playhead'' (red, with diamond marker and time label)
* ''Region playback playhead'' (green, with dot marker)

---

!!!! Toolbar Controls

|!Button |!Description |h
|🔍 Zoom to Region |Zoom the view to the selected region + padding |
|↔ Full Track |Reset to full track view |
|▶ Play / ⏹ Stop |Play or stop the selected region |
|🎯 Set Start / Set End |Enter listen mode: audio plays and you tap to set the handle position |
|🔁 Loop |Toggle loop playback of the selected region |
|⏮ Pre-roll |Play 3s before and 2s after the start handle |
|⏭ Post-roll |Play 2s before and 3s after the end handle |
|🧲 Snap to Silence |Snap both handles to the nearest silence boundary |
|🔊 Amplitude slider |Vertical zoom to amplify quiet sections (1×–8×) |
|🎤 Transcribe |Send the selected region to ~OpenAI Whisper |

---

!!!! Interaction

* ''Drag handles'' to adjust start/end times with live scrub audio
* ''Shift+drag inside region'' to slide both handles together
* ''Click & drag outside region'' (or inside without Shift) to pan/scroll the timeline
* ''Click minimap'' to center the view at that point
* ''Auto-pan'' when dragging near canvas edges (quadratic acceleration)

---

!!!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Key |!Action |h
|`←` / `→` |Nudge last-dragged handle ±1s |
|`Shift+←` / `Shift+→` |Nudge ±5s |
|`S` |Snap last-dragged handle to nearest silence |
|`Shift+S` |Snap both handles to silence |
|`T` |Transcribe selected region |
|`Ctrl+Z` |Undo |
|`Ctrl+Shift+Z` / `Ctrl+Y` |Redo |
|`Space` / `Enter` (in listen mode) |Mark the time |
|`Escape` (in listen mode) |Cancel listen mode |

---

!!!! Audio Loading Pipeline

# ''Metadata preload'' — An `<audio>` element loads metadata for a quick duration
# ''Cache check'' — If peaks/duration are cached, render immediately
# ''Full decode'' — Fetch and decode the audio via Web Audio API for waveform peaks and ~AudioBuffer playback
# ''Fallback'' — If fetch/decode fails, uses metadata-only duration with a flat track visualization

---

!!!! Playback Strategies

# ''~AudioBuffer'' (preferred) — Sample-accurate, uses Web Audio API `AudioBufferSourceNode`
# ''HTML Audio'' (fallback) — Uses a standard `<audio>` element with `currentTime` seeking
# ''VBR adjustment'' — Automatically compensates for VBR MP3 duration mismatches between decoded and playback durations

