!!! `<$sound-effect>`

A lightweight widget for triggering audio playback. Useful for one-shot sounds, snippet playback from captures, or event-driven audio.

---

!!!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Description |h
|`src` |`""` |Direct URL to the audio file. |
|`tiddler` |`""` |Tiddler title to resolve audio from (uses `resolveAudioSrc`). |
|`volume` |`"1"` |Playback volume (0–1). |
|`autoplay` |`"no"` |Play immediately on render. |
|`startTime` |`""` |Start time in seconds for snippet playback. |
|`endTime` |`""` |End time in seconds. If equal to `startTime` or absent, plays 20s (or to track end). |
|`trigger` |`"click"` |Trigger mode: `"click"` (click the widget), `"event"` (listen to event bus), or `"none"`. |
|`event` |`""` |Event name to listen for when `trigger="event"`. |

---

!!!! Event Payload

When triggered via event, the data payload can include:

* `audioSource` — tiddler title to resolve
* `startSeconds` / `endSeconds` — playback range
* `startTime` / `endTime` — alternative string forms

