!! Configuration

---

!!! Notation Title Template

Set `$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/notationTitleTemplate` to customize how notation tiddler titles are generated.

''Default:'' `$:/annotations/{safeParent}/{start}-{end}`

''Placeholders:''

|!Placeholder |!Value |h
|`{parent}` |Raw parent tiddler title |
|`{safeParent}` |Sanitized parent title (safe for paths) |
|`{start}` |Start time in seconds |
|`{end}` |End time in seconds |
|`{start_time}` |Formatted start time (e.g., `05:23`) |
|`{end_time}` |Formatted end time |

A numeric suffix is appended automatically if the title already exists.

---

!!! Default Notation Tags

Set `$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/defaultNotationTags` to a space-separated list of tags that will be added to every new notation tiddler (in addition to the parent tiddler tag).

---

!!! Transcription Configuration

All transcription settings are stored under `$:/plugins/NoteStreams/AudioSuite/configuration/transcriptions/`:

|!Tiddler (suffix) |!Default |!Description |h
|`api-key` |//(required)// |Your ~OpenAI API key |
|`model` |`whisper-1` |Whisper model name |
|`language` |`""` |ISO language code (e.g., `en`). Empty = auto-detect |
|`endpoint` |`https://api.openai.com/v1/audio/transcriptions` |Whisper API endpoint |
|`prompt` |`""` |Optional prompt to guide Whisper |
|`editor-model` |`gpt-4.1-nano` |LLM model for post-editing transcriptions |
|`editor-prompt` |//(built-in)// |System prompt for the editor pass |
|`editor-endpoint` |`https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions` |Chat completions endpoint |
|`editor-enabled` |`true` |Set to `false` to skip the editor pass |

The transcription result is stored in the `transcription` field of the notation tiddler. Subsequent transcriptions are appended with a `---` separator.

---

!! Event Bus

~AudioSuite widgets communicate via a lightweight internal event bus. Key events:

|!Event |!Emitter |!Listener |!Payload |h
|`AudioSuite:timecode-captured` |`<$podcast-player>` |`<$audio-notation>` |`{ startSeconds, endSeconds, startTimecode, endTimecode, track, audioSrc, audioPointer, srcField, skipEditor, userTags, ... }` |
|`AudioSuite:seek` |`<$audio-notation>` (badge click) |`<$podcast-player>` |`{ seconds, track, audioSource }` |
|`AudioSuite:notation-editor-closed` |`<$audio-notation>` |`<$podcast-player>` |`{ saved, entryTitle, skipEditor }` |

The seek event supports ''cross-track seeks'' in audiobook mode — clicking a timecode badge from a different chapter automatically loads that chapter and seeks to the correct position.

---

!! Audio Source Resolution

The `resolveAudioSrc` utility resolves audio sources from tiddlers in the following priority order:

# Preferred field (if specified) → checks if value is a tiddler title and resolves its canonical URI
# `_canonical_uri` / `canonical_uri` / `canonicalUri`
# `src` / `url` fields
# Inline base64 audio (tiddler with `type: audio/*` and base64 text content → `data:` URI)

---

!! Theming & Palette Integration

All visual components resolve colors from:

# ''CSS custom properties'' (e.g., `--palette-accent`, `--palette-fg`)
# ''~TiddlyWiki `$:/palette` tiddler'' key-value pairs (e.g., `accent`, `foreground`, `page-background`)
# ''Hardcoded defaults'' as a final fallback

The notation widget applies palette values as CSS custom properties on `document.documentElement` so the accompanying stylesheet can reference them. The waveform editor sets palette variables as inline custom properties on its wrapper element.

