!! Example Usage

---

!!! Basic Podcast Player with Annotations

```
<$podcast-player filter="[tag[Episodes]sort[title]]" srcField="audio-url">
  <$audio-notation />
</$podcast-player>
```

---

!!! Audiobook with Chapter Navigation

```
<$podcast-player
  filter="[tag[MyBook Chapters]sort[order]]"
  srcField="audio-file"
  mode="audiobook"
  bookTiddler="MyBook"
  rewindOnResume="5"
>
  <$audio-notation bookTiddler="MyBook" />
</$podcast-player>
```

---

!!! Waveform Editor in a Notation Tiddler

```
<$waveform-editor
  audio-source={{!!audio-source}}
  startTime={{!!start-seconds}}
  endTime={{!!end-seconds}}
  tiddler=<<currentTiddler>>
  width="700"
  height="140"
/>
```

---

!!! Sound Effect Triggered by Event

```
<$sound-effect tiddler="NotificationSound" trigger="event" event="my-custom-event" volume="0.5" />
```

---

!! Browser Compatibility

* Requires ''Web Audio API'' support (all modern browsers)
* Uses ''Pointer Events'' with mouse/touch fallbacks
* Uses ''`<canvas>`'' for waveform rendering
* ''Fetch API'' for audio loading and transcription API calls
* Tested on desktop and mobile (includes mobile detection and modal UI)

---

!! Architecture Notes

The plugin is organised into focused modules:

|!Module |!Role |h
|`audio-utils.js` |Shared utilities: time formatting, title generation, event bus, source resolution |
|`waveform-renderer.js` |Pure rendering functions for canvas (waveform + minimap) |
|`sound-effects-widget.js` |Lightweight `<$sound-effect>` widget |
|`podcast-player-widget.js` |Main player widget with playlist, transport, capture workflow |
|`audio-notation-widget.js` |Notation display/editing widget with atomic tiddler storage |
|`waveform-editor-widget.js` |Visual waveform region editor with transcription |
|`audio-cache.js` |In-memory cache for decoded audio, peaks, view state, undo stacks |
|`audio-loader.js` |Fetch + decode pipeline with progress callbacks |
|`mp3-parser.js` |MP3 frame header parsing, VBR/Xing header support, byte-level seeking |
|`wav-encoder.js` |WAV encoding from ~AudioBuffer regions for Whisper API |
|`peaks-generator.js` |Waveform peak extraction from decoded ~AudioBuffer |

All widgets extend the ~TiddlyWiki `Widget` base class and follow the standard `execute` → `render` → `refresh` → `removeChildDomNodes` lifecycle. Cleanup is thorough — every widget removes event listeners, pauses audio elements, clears timers, and releases resources on teardown.